    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ══ Capacity ══ -->
  <h2 id="capacity">Capacity</h2>

  <p>An industrial centrifuge capacity (throughput) is the volume of fluid the centrifuge can process in a given time. A <strong>decanter-type industrial centrifuge</strong> can process <strong>5 to 300+ gallons per minute</strong>. An <strong>industrial disc centrifuge</strong> has a capacity range of <strong>1 to 200+ GPM</strong>. The actual processing capacity depends on the process fluid and contaminant level.</p>

